    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. When you say the second area has \"greater market uncertainty,\" are you implying that the rapid demographic shifts and high turnover inherently make the neighborhood less stable for long-term investment? Like, would those demographic changes be a factor in predicting whether property values hold up or drop over a 10-year period?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
