      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, rapid demographic shifts and high turnover inherently introduce greater market uncertainty. A high turnover rate can signal that residents are primarily renters or temporary occupants, which can lead to less consistent long-term investment in the immediate physical property. While the area might see short-term rental spikes, the lack of entrenched community roots can make predicting sustained, long-term appreciation more difficult than in a settled neighborhood.",
      "source": "target",
